The '''Sylhet Oakblue''' (''Amblypodia  silhetensis'')<ref name="LepIndex silhetensis">[http://internt.nhm.ac.uk/jdsml/research-curation/projects/lepindex/detail.dsml?TaxonNo=195037.0&UserID=&UserName=&&listPageURL=list%2edsml%3fSCIENTIFIC%5fNAME%5fon%5fcardqtype%3dstarts%2bwith%26sort%3dSCIENTIFIC%255fNAME%255fon%255fcard%26SCIENTIFIC%5fNAME%5fon%5fcard%3dsilhetensis%26recLimit%3d30&searchPageURL=index%2edsml%3fsort%3dSCIENTIFIC%255fNAME%255fon%255fcard%26SCIENTIFIC%5fNAME%5fon%5fcardqtype%3dstarts%2bwith%26SCIENTIFIC%5fNAME%5fon%5fcard%3dsilhetensis%26recLimit%3d30 Card for  '''''silhetensis''''' in LepIndex. Accessed 16 Jun 2007.]</ref> is a small [[butterfly]] found in [[India]] that belongs to the [[Lycaenidae|Lycaenids or Blues]] family.
[[Image:Arhsilf.jpg|thumb|230pz|left|Museum specimen Female]]
==Range==
The butterfly occurs in [[India]] from [[Sikkim]] onto north [[Myanmar]], and, from [[Karens]] to south [[Myanmar]].
<ref name="Evans">Evans,W.H.(1932) The Identification of Indian Butterflies, ser no H49.21, pp 260.</ref>

==Status==
Rare.<ref name="Evans"/>

